<div id="review_3429786860" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3429786860" />
    <a title="Howardstein" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/99772449-howardstein"><img alt="Howardstein" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1562995300p2/99772449.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3429786860?book_show_action=true">Jul 06, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Howardstein" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Howardstein" href="/user/show/99772449-howardstein">Howardstein</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3429786860" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17680105918612497688">I can&apos;t complain, it was very insightful and not like fantasy. It&apos;s what I expect from sci fi. Glad to have read this as a sequel to The Time Machine written 100 years ago, it really explored the ideas and universe much more, and after reading the Time Ships I was convinced that the Time Machine had been an incomplete book. It had more potential and this book actualized it. Not all of the parts are riveting to read and I could go with skipping some of the boring descriptions and narration of ins</span>
  <span id="freeText17680105918612497688" style="display:none">I can't complain, it was very insightful and not like fantasy. It's what I expect from sci fi. Glad to have read this as a sequel to The Time Machine written 100 years ago, it really explored the ideas and universe much more, and after reading the Time Ships I was convinced that the Time Machine had been an incomplete book. It had more potential and this book actualized it. Not all of the parts are riveting to read and I could go with skipping some of the boring descriptions and narration of insignificant things, so that's why I lean towards 4.7 stars, and I rounded up not just because of math but because the book compensated with the story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17680105918612497688" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
